---
title: Seitan and Black Bean Chili with Bell Pepper and Cheddar Cheese over Jasmine Rice
description: While beans are the basis for any good vegetarian chili, sometimes you just want a little bit more oomph in your bowl. Here, we’re using seitan to lend extra heartiness to this dish. Seasoned with chorizo spices, the wheat-based protein has smoky, sultry flavor built right in. Served on top a bed of white rice and garnished with shreds of melty cheese, this chili is comfort food at its finest.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/chipotle-seitan-chili-1aca3f82.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chipotle-seitan-chili-da033fc5.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/chipotle-seitan-chili-59f25211053468022f68a2f2
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 730 kcal
  fat: 14 g
  saturated fat: 3 g
  carbohydrates: 91 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 54 g
  fiber: 22 g
  sodium: 940 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: North America
---

Bring 1 cup water to a boil in a #small pot{}. Once boiling, add @Jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, cover, and reduce to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until rest of meal is ready.

Wash and dry all produce. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}(minced or grated). Core and seed @red bell pepper{1}(cored and seeded), then finely dice. Halve, peel, and dice @red onion{1}(peeled and diced). Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and sliced), keeping greens and whites separate. Core and dice @Roma tomato{1}(cored and diced). Drain and rinse @black beans{1%box}(drained and rinsed).

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add pepper, onion, and scallion whites. Cook, tossing, until softened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir garlic, tomato, and @veggie chorizo crumbles{8%ounce} into pan, breaking up seitan into small pieces. Cook, tossing, until tomato softens, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir black beans, @veggie stock concentrate{1}(stock concentrate), and 1 cup water into pan. Bring to a simmer and let bubble until thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between plates. Top with chili. Garnish with scallion greens and @cheddar cheese{1/4%cup}(shredded).

> While beans are the basis for any good vegetarian chili, sometimes you just want a little bit more oomph in your bowl. Here, we're using seitan to lend extra heartiness to this dish. Seasoned with chorizo spices, the wheat-based protein has smoky, sultry flavor built right in. Served on top a bed of white rice and garnished with shreds of melty cheese, this chili is comfort food at its finest.